Enjoy your own tropical oasis with this Disney’s Stitch inspired Grilled Tropical Split 🍍🍓🍌🫐🍦 

 

🍍🍓🍌🫐🍦🍍🍓🍌🫐🍦🍍🍓🍌🫐🍦🍍🍓🍌🫐🍦 

 

Ingredients 

3 DOLE® Bananas, 2 peeled & frozen, 1 peeled 

8 chunks fresh DOLE Tropical Gold® Pineapple 

2 peaches, pitted and quartered 

Olive Oil Spray 

1 teaspoon ground cinnamon 

1 cup Fresh Berry Sauce (see recipe below) 

2 tablespoons chopped toasted almonds 

4 mint sprigs 

 

Directions 

1. Press the two frozen bananas through Yonanas® machine into a cup. If you don’t have a Yonanas machine; peel, slice and freeze bananas for 2 hours. Place frozen banana slices in food processor or blender. Cover; blend until bananas become a smooth custard. Keep in the freezer until ready to serve. 

2. Preheat grill or broiler to high. 

3. Cut remaining banana into eight pieces. Alternately thread banana, pineapple and peach wedges onto skewers. Spray fruit with olive oil spray and season with cinnamon. Grill on all sides or until fruit is softened and light brown around edges. 

 4. Arrange skewers on serving plates with a scoop of the frozen banana, a spoonful of Fresh Berry Sauce, a sprinkling of almonds and mint. 

Fresh Berry Sauce: In a saucepan, combine 1/2 cup quartered DOLE® Strawberries, 1/4 cup DOLE Blueberries and 1/4 cup DOLE Blackberries with 2 tablespoons water and 1 tablespoon honey. Warm the berries until they soften. Remove from heat and add 1/4 cup DOLE Raspberries. Set aside until ready to use.

Happy Fourth of July 💛 We hope everyone has a safe and celebratory day full of fresh fruit and laughter 🎇🍓🥥🫐 

 Check out the 4th of July Fruit Tart recipe below 😋

🎇🍓🥥🫐🎇🍓🥥🫐🎇🍓🥥🫐🎇🍓🥥🫐🎇🍓🥥🫐🎇🍓🥥🫐 

 

Ingredients 

Nonstick cooking spray 

½ cup sliced almonds 

2 tablespoons unsweetened coconut flakes 

½ cup mashed DOLE® Avocado 

1½ tablespoons honey 

1 cup old-fashioned rolled oats 

1 teaspoon ground cinnamon 

1 container (5.3 ounces) vanilla almond milk yogurt alternative 

2 DOLE® Bananas, cut into thirds 

1 teaspoon vanilla extract 

2 teaspoons powdered gelatin 

½ cup unsweetened almond milk 

½ cup sliced DOLE® Strawberries 

½ cup DOLE® Blueberries 

 

Directions 

Preheat oven to 325°F. Spray 9-inch tart pan or round baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Process almonds and coconut in food processor 30 seconds or until fine crumbs form. 

Whisk avocado and honey in a medium bowl; stir in oats, ½ teaspoon cinnamon and almond-coconut mixture. Press into bottom and up sides of prepared pan; bake 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Cool completely. 

Purée yogurt, bananas, vanilla extract and remaining ½ teaspoon cinnamon in a blender on high 1 minute or until smooth; transfer to medium bowl. Makes about 1¼ cups. 

Sprinkle gelatin over 2 tablespoons cold water in a cup; let stand 5 minutes. Heat almond milk in small saucepan over medium heat 5 minutes or until hot; whisk in gelatin mixture until dissolved, then whisk into yogurt mixture. Pour filling into crust; refrigerate at least 2 hours or until set. 

Arrange strawberries and blueberries on top of tart; cut into 8 slices.

You’ll want to save this Disney’s Stitch inspired Hawaiian slaw recipe for your block party this weekend 😉🍍🤤 

 

🍍🍔🌭🍍🍔🌭🍍🍔🌭🍍🍔🌭🍍🍔🌭🍍🍔🌭🍍🍔🌭🍍🍔🌭 

 

Ingredients 

2 tablespoons DOLE® Pineapple Juice 

2 tablespoons canola oil 

1 tablespoon rice vinegar 

1 teaspoon raw cane sugar 

½ teaspoon gluten free garlic powder 

½ teaspoon gluten free onion powder 

¼ teaspoon gluten free chili powder 

¼ teaspoon kosher salt 

1/8 teaspoon gluten free smoked paprika 

2 cups thinly sliced DOLE® Green Cabbage 

½ cup DOLE® Shredded Carrots 

½ cup thinly sliced DOLE® Red Cabbage 

1 teaspoon toasted sesame seeds 

½ teaspoon dried parsley 

 

Directions 

Whisk pineapple juice, oil, vinegar, sugar, garlic powder, onion powder, chili powder, salt and paprika in a large bowl; fold in green cabbage, carrots, red cabbage, sesame seeds and parsley. Makes about 2½ cups.
